me.hyperperform.reporting

Class ReportGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.hyperperform.reporting.ReportGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IReport

    public class ReportGenerator
extends Object
implements IReport
    A realization of the IReport interface. All three contracts defined in IReport have been met. Report generators can be easily plugged in and out as long as the contract is met.

    • Method Detail

      • getSummary

        public GetSummaryResponse getSummary(GetSummaryRequest getSummaryRequest)
        Generates a summary for all the event data received within a specific time span. Summaries are generated for each integration which currently exist. Each summary is independent from the others.
        Specified by:
        getSummary in interface IReport
        Parameters:
        getSummaryRequest - Request object which contains the necessary details for the summary, this includes the name of the user for whom the summary will be for as well as a time period.
        Returns:
        The response object contains the summaries for each individual integration.

      • getDetails

        public GetDetailsResponse getDetails(GetDetailsRequest getDetailsRequest)
        Generates a detailed report for a specified integration. These reports also require a user and time span. The type of integration for which the detailed report is required must be specified every time a request is made.
        Specified by:
        getDetails in interface IReport
        Parameters:
        getDetailsRequest - Request object which contains the necessary details for the summary, this includes the name of the user for whom the summary will be for as well as a time period.
        Returns:
        Returns an object which contains detailed information for a specific integration.

      • getScore

        public GetScoreResponse getScore(GetScoreRequest getScoreRequest)
        Generates a performance score for a specified user. Score generation also requires a user and time span. Each score is generated using an Algorithm.
        Specified by:
        getScore in interface IReport
        Parameters:
        getScoreRequest - Request object which contains the necessary details for the summary, this includes the name of the user for whom the score will be for as well as a time period.
        Returns:
        Returns an object which contains the performance score for a particular employee.
